description:
  We obtain a classification of a Q-factorial Q-Fano 3-fold $X$ with the
following properties:
  the Picard number of $X$ is 1;
  the Gorenstein index of $X$ is 2;
  the Fano index of $X$ is 1/2;
  $h^0 (-K_X) \geq 4$;
  there exists an index 2 point $P$ such that $(X,P)\simeq (\{xy +f(z^2,u)=0\}
/ \Bbb Z_2 (1,1,1,0), o)$ with $ord f(Z,U)=1$.
